The paper discusses phishing attacks and their impact on users, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on user studies and social engineering techniques, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybercrime (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential solutions to prevent phishing attacks, which can be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of phishing attacks on productivity and financial losses, which can be related to social informatics (cs.SI).
